    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Swift to its close ebbs out life’s little day;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Earth’s joys grow dim, its glories pass away;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Change and decay in all around I see;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "O Thou who changest not, abide with me."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "2"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Come not in terrors, as the King of kings;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But kind and good, with healing in Thy wings:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Tears for all woes, a heart for every plea;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Come, Friend of sinners, thus abide with me."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "3"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I need Thy presence every passing hour:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "What but Thy grace can foil the tempter’s power?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Who like Thyself my guide and stay can be?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Through cloud and sunshine, oh, abide with me."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "4"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I fear no foe, with Thee at hand to bless:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Ills have no weight, and tears no bitterness:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Where is death’s sting? where, grave, thy victory?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I triumph still, if Thou abide with me."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "5"
    }
